#31000
The Frjosa Hel-vegr Tundra~
   Looking in any direction proves to be pointless, as it is all white.  
Although, to the west there seems to be a large wall of ice running north and
south.  Visibility is three to five feet at best.  The ground is frozen solid,
the air painfully dry and cold, and the wind feels like daggers.  This is no
place for any sane being.  Unless, you're a polar bear or a dire wolf, you
best find shelter and fire soon.  
~
310 64 0 0 0 13
D1
~
~
